        <!-- ============================================================
             HOW TO ADD A NEW RELEASE
             ============================================================
             1. Build & archive SequenceSuite Pro Direct, export as notarised DMG
             2. Run the Sparkle signing tool against the DMG:
                    ./bin/sign_update SequenceSuite-1.0.dmg
                This prints an edSignature value and a length. Copy both.
             3. Duplicate the <item> block below, fill in:
                    - <title>          human version string
                    - sparkle:version  CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION (integer build number)
                    - sparkle:shortVersionString  MARKETING_VERSION (e.g. 1.0)
                    - <pubDate>        release date (RFC 2822 format)
                    - url              direct download link to the DMG
                    - sparkle:edSignature  the signature from step 2
                    - length           file size in bytes from step 2
             4. Create a GitHub Release tagged vX.Y.Z in editkit-tools/sequencesuite,
                attach the DMG renamed to SequenceSuite.dmg.
                Commit the updated appcast.xml to the repo root — GitHub Pages
                serves it at https://editkit-tools.github.io/sequencesuite/appcast.xml.
             ============================================================ -->

